        "@language": "en",
        "@value": "Fuel Cell"
      }
    ],
    "http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf": [
      {
        "@id": "https://www.commoncoreontologies.org/ont00001049"
      }
    ],
    "http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition": [
      {
        "@language": "en",
        "@value": "An Electrical Power Source that consists in part of an anode, a cathode, and an electrolyte; converts chemical energy from a fuel into electricity through a chemical reaction of positively charged hydrogen ions with an oxidizing agent (typically oxygen); and, if given a continuous source of fuel and oxidizing agent, can continuously produce electricity."
      }
    ],
    "http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#scopeNote": [
      {
        "@language": "en",
        "@value": "A Fuel Cell differs from a Battery in that it requires a continuous source of fuel and oxygen to sustain the chemical reaction, whereas a Battery only uses chemicals already stored inside it."
      }
    ],
    "https://www.commoncoreontologies.org/ont00001754": [
      {
        "@type": "http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#anyURI",
        "@value": "https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Fuel_cell&oldid=1063586731"
      }
    ],
    "https://www.commoncoreontologies.org/ont00001760": [
      {
        "@type": "http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#anyURI",
        "@value": "https://www.commoncoreontologies.org/ArtifactOntology"
      }
    ]
  },
